Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   This session is a continuation of work on "xpabat," a bat spectrogram viewer Flask web app. The session covered five sequential requests:
   1. **(Resumed from previous)** Call rendering performance: pre-draw calls to an offscreen canvas so zoomed-out renders cost a single `drawImage()` blit instead of O(n_calls).
   2. Fix pixelated/blocky call rendering around the 22s zoom level — the cache was activating too early with a bad scale factor.
   3. Double-click a call to: select it, zoom/center on it (same as call-ID text box), and place an orange marquee around its bounding box to set up audio loop + BPF filter.
   4. Previous/next call navigation: if the current call has a matching marquee (bounds equal call bounding box), carry the marquee to the next call; otherwise clear any marquee.
   5. **(In progress, hit token limit)** Fix aliasing/shimmer when translating/zooming the spectrogram — specifically calls flickering in/out of visibility at sub-pixel widths due to inadequate downsampling filter.

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Canvas 2D offscreen rendering for call tick pre-render cache (`_callsCC`)
   - `imageSmoothingEnabled` / `imageSmoothingQuality` ('low'/'medium'/'high') for drawImage resampling
   - Bilinear (medium) vs Lanczos3 (high) downsampling — at 270:1 ratio bilinear only samples 2 of 270 source pixels, causing aliasing that looks like nearest-neighbor
   - LOD (Level of Detail) threshold (`LOD_DUR_THRESHOLD`) governing when full contour rendering vs batched ticks vs cache blit is used
   - `SPARSE_THRESHOLD = 400` calls: below this, full `drawCall()` with contours per call; above, batched ticks
   - Ruler/marquee system: `S.rulerX0/Y0/X1/Y1` (pixel-space), `S.rulerLoopT0/T1/F0/F1` (absolute time/freq), `S.rulerFixed`
   - Viewport ordering: `zoomToCall(c)` updates `S.viewStart/S.viewDur` synchronously, so `tToX`/`fToY` must be called AFTER it to get correct pixel coords for the ruler
   - `_marqueeMatchesCall(c)`: compares absolute loop bounds against call's t0/t1/Fmin/Fmax using `===` (exact match, no epsilon needed since they were copied verbatim)
   - Tile warp cache in coords.js (`_getWarpedTile`): pre-warps each tile image to canvas height H for log/linear frequency blending; already uses `'high'` quality for the warp step itself
   - Call cache refPPS: `Math.max(1, Math.min(10, Math.floor(16384 / Math.max(S.duration, 1))))` — adapts to keep cache canvas within Safari's 16,384px limit

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`/Users/brandon/claude/xpabat/static/render.js`**
     - Added call render cache variables and `_ensureCallsCC(H)` before `drawCallsBatched`:
     ```javascript
     let _callsCC     = null;   // offscreen HTMLCanvasElement
     let _callsCCKey  = '';     // fingerprint of last build
     let _callsCCPPS  = 10;     // refPPS stored when _callsCC was last built

     function _callsCCFingerprint(H) {
       const hidden = [...S.hiddenSpecies].sort().join(',');
       return `${S.freqLow}|${S.freqHigh}|${S.logScale.toFixed(3)}|${S.minConf}|${hidden}|${H}|${S.calls.length}|${S.classifier}`;
     }

     function _ensureCallsCC(H) {
       const key = _callsCCFingerprint(H);
       if (key === _callsCCKey && _callsCC) return _callsCC;
       const refPPS = Math.max(1, Math.min(10, Math.floor(16384 / Math.max(S.duration, 1))));
       const CW = Math.ceil(S.duration * refPPS);
       if (CW < 1 || H < 1) return null;
       if (!_callsCC || _callsCC.width !== CW || _callsCC.height !== H) {
         _callsCC = document.createElement('canvas');
         _callsCC.width  = CW;
         _callsCC.height = H;
       }
       const cctx = _callsCC.getContext('2d');
       cctx.clearRect(0, 0, CW, H);
       const bySpecies = {};
       for (const c of S.calls) {
         if (S.hiddenSpecies.has(c.species) || c.conf < S.minConf) continue;
         if (!bySpecies[c.species]) bySpecies[c.species] = { col: c.color, calls: [] };
         bySpecies[c.species].calls.push(c);
       }
       for (const { col, calls } of Object.values(bySpecies)) {
         cctx.fillStyle = col;
         cctx.beginPath();
         for (const c of calls) {
           const xc = (c.t0 + c.t1) * 0.5 * refPPS;
           const y0 = fToY(c.Fmax);
           const y1 = fToY(c.Fmin);
           cctx.rect(xc - 1, y0, 2, Math.max(2, y1 - y0));
         }
         cctx.fill();
       }
       _callsCCKey = key;
       _callsCCPPS = refPPS;
       return _callsCC;
     }
     ```

     - `drawCallsBatched` rewritten:
     ```javascript
     function drawCallsBatched(visible, specW, H) {
       // Zoomed-out path: blit the pre-rendered cache once viewDur is large enough
       // that the cache's 10 px/s reference resolution maps close to 1:1 on screen.
       if (S.viewDur > 120) {
         const cc = _ensureCallsCC(H);
         if (cc) {
           const srcX = S.viewStart * _callsCCPPS;
           const srcW = Math.max(1, S.viewDur * _callsCCPPS);
           ctx.globalAlpha = S.contourAlpha;
           ctx.drawImage(cc, srcX, 0, srcW, H, YAXIS_W, 0, specW, H);
           ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
           return;
         }
       }
       // Live draw: for viewDur <= 120s or cache not ready
       const tickW = Math.max(2, _baseLineW());
       const half  = tickW / 2;
       const bySpecies = {};
       for (const c of visible) {
         if (!bySpecies[c.species]) bySpecies[c.species] = { col: c.color, calls: [] };
         bySpecies[c.species].calls.push(c);
       }
       for (const { col, calls } of Object.values(bySpecies)) {
         ctx.fillStyle   = col;
         ctx.globalAlpha = S.contourAlpha;
         ctx.beginPath();
         for (const c of calls) {
           const xc = tToX((c.t0 + c.t1) / 2);
           const y0 = fToY(c.Fmax);
           const y1 = fToY(c.Fmin);
           ctx.rect(xc - half, y0, tickW, Math.max(tickW, y1 - y0));
         }
         ctx.fill();
       }
       ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
     }
