2. Key Technical Concepts:

- **Leaflet.js**: Open-source map library loaded from CDN (unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4)
- **COEP `require-corp`**: Cross-Origin Embedder Policy blocks external CDN resources unless they have `Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin`; solved by server-side tile proxy
- **Tile proxy**: Flask route `/api/maptile/<s>/<z>/<x>/<y>.png` fetches CartoDB dark tiles server-side with in-process LRU cache (2000 entries), returning them as same-origin responses
- **Pre-rendered offscreen canvas blit pattern**: Build a canvas once keyed on zoom/filter state; only srcX changes on scroll (no per-frame recompute)
- **pxPerSec exact float**: Must use `specW / S.viewDur` (not `Math.round(...)`) to prevent call ticks drifting from spectrogram features
- **MAX_CALL_CANVAS_W = 8192**: If `S.duration * pxPerSec > 8192`, skip pre-rendered canvas and use per-frame `drawCallsBatched()` to avoid ~600MB canvas allocation
- **WebGL `LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST`**: Replaced `LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR` (trilinear) — snaps to nearest mip level instead of blending between levels, eliminates softness at near-1:1 zoom
- **Batched stroke calls**: In sparse path, group all non-sel/non-hov call contours by species color into one `beginPath+stroke` per species instead of one stroke per call — reduces ~400 stroke() calls/frame to ~5
- **Pre-rendered overview calls canvas**: `_ovCallsCanvas`/`_ovCallsKey` offscreen canvas rebuilt only when calls/filter/freq viewport/overview window changes; saves ~8-9% per-frame CPU from per-frame `beginPath+fill` on all calls
- **URL sync throttle**: `_scheduleURLSync()` was called from every `scheduleRender()` call (60fps) causing clearTimeout+setTimeout churn; added 50ms minimum interval guard
- **`ctx.beginPath()+rect()+fill()` vs individual `fillRect()`**: In Firefox, batched path fill uses slow Skia antialiased edge walker for small rects. In Chrome, batched fill is FASTER than individual fillRect (fewer JS→native calls). This matters for `drawCallRug`.
- **Firefox `_getWarpedTileBlit` 25.3%**: Firefox doesn't accelerate WebGL→Canvas2D compositing on GPU; Chrome stays on GPU and this is near-free
- **Chrome `set innerHTML` mystery**: 14.4% of active time in second Chrome trace, callers unresolved

